{{nihongo|'''''Indian Summer'''''|<U+3053><U+306F><U+308B><U+3073><U+3088><U+308A>|Koharu Biyori|lead=yes}} is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] [[manga]] written and illustrated by [[Takehito Mizuki]]. The manga was serialised in [[MediaWorks (publisher)|MediaWorks]]'s monthly ''[[Dengeki Daioh]]'' before MediaWorks moved the title to the quarterly ''[[Dengeki Moeoh]]''. The manga is licensed in [[English language|English]] by [[ComicsOne]].

==Characters==
*{{nihongo|'''Yui'''|<U+3086><U+3044>|Yui}} is the female protagonist and Takaya's robot maid. {{Voiced by|[[Eri Kitamura]]}}<ref name="Newtype USA 6 12 16">"Koharubiyori" ''Newtype USA'' '''6''' (12) 16. December 2007. {{ISSN|1541-4817}}.</ref>
*{{nihongo|'''Takaya Murase'''|<U+6751><U+702C><U+8CB4><U+4E5F>|Murase Takaya}} is the male protagonist and Yui's owner. He has a maid fetish and is good at cooking and sewing.{{Voiced by|[[Takayuki Kondou]]}}<ref name="Newtype USA 6 12 16"/>
*{{nihongo|'''Minori  Sumitomo'''|<U+4F4F><U+53CB><U+307F><U+306E><U+308A>|Sumitomo Minori}} likes Takaya and works as a maid in her dad's cafe, Cafe Cowbeya. {{Voiced by|[[Satomi Akesaka]]}}<ref name="Newtype USA 6 12 16"/>
*{{nihongo|'''Tetsushi  Sumitomo'''|<U+4F4F><U+53CB><U+54F2><U+5FD7>|Sumitomo Tetsushi}} is Minori's father and Cafe Cowbeya's owner. {{Voiced by|[[Kenta Miyake]]}}
*{{nihongo|'''Tenchou'''|<U+5E97><U+9577>|Tenchou}} is the shop manager. {{Voiced by|[[Kaya Miyake]]}}
*{{nihongo|'''Ayumi Hagiwara'''|<U+8429><U+539F><U+6B69><U+7F8E>|Hagiwara Ayumi}} {{Voiced by|[[Yuka Iguchi]]}}
*{{nihongo|'''Kanae Hagiwara'''|<U+8429><U+539F><U+9999><U+82D7>|Hagiwara Kanae}} is Ayumi's mother. {{Voiced by|[[Ryouka Yuzuki]]}}
*{{nihongo|'''Ran Midou'''|<U+5FA1><U+5802><U+862D>|Midou Ran}} is the younger sister of Sumire. {{Voiced by|[[Sayuri Yahagi]]}}
*{{nihongo|'''Sumire Midou'''|<U+5FA1><U+5802><U+83EB>|Midou Sumire}} is the older sister of Ran. {{Voiced by|[[Saori Hayami]]}}
*{{nihongo|'''Sakuya'''|<U+3055><U+304F><U+3084>|Sakuya}} is Takaya's ultimate customized figurine. {{Voiced by|[[Ai Shimizu]]}}

==Media==

===Manga===
''Koharu Biyori'' is written and illustrated by Takehito Mizuki. The manga was serialised in [[MediaWorks (publisher)|MediaWorks]]'s monthly ''[[Dengeki Daioh]]'' before MediaWorks moved the title to the quarterly ''[[Dengeki Moeoh]]''. The manga is licensed in North America by [[ComicsOne]]. The English license was transferred to [[DrMaster]] after ComicsOne's collapse.<ref name="Mania"/> As of February, 2009, MediaWorks has published 4 ''[[tank<U+014D>bon|bound volumes]]'' of the manga. [[ComicsOne]] released the first volume of the manga on February 16, 2005.<ref name="A"/> The manga is licensed in Taiwan by [[Ever Glory Publishing]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.egmanga.com.tw/Manga2005/03_gbooks/eggbooks27.jsp?no=3957|title=<U+6A5F><U+68B0><U+5973><U+50D5><U+FF0E><U+6DF1><U+6708><U+305F><U+3051><U+3072><U+3068>|trans_title=''Koharu Biyori''|publisher=[[Ever Glory Publishing]]|language=Chinese|accessdate=21 November 2009}}</ref>

