===Soundtrack CDs===
On November 21, 2007, [[Geneon]] released an animation soundtrack CD for ''Koharu Biyori''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=GNCA-1137|title=Koharu Biyori Original Soundtrack |publisher=cdjapan.co.jp|accessdate=2009-03-22}}</ref> 

[[Geneon]] released two ''Maniac'' CDs for ''Koharu Biyori''. The first CD, ''Koharu Biyori Maniacs CD 1'' was released on December 21, 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=GNCA-1138|title=Koharu Biyori Maniacs CD 1 |publisher=cdjapan.co.jp|accessdate=2009-03-22}}</ref> The second CD, ''Koharu Biyori Maniacs CD 2'' was released on February 22, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=GNCA-1139|title=Koharu Biyori Maniacs CD 2 |publisher=cdjapan.co.jp|accessdate=2009-03-22}}</ref> The songs are sung by the [[seiy<U+016B>|voice actors/actresses]] of the characters.

==Reception==
Mania.com's Eduardo M. Chavez criticised the manga for having "no plot" and a cast that "lacks personality". He also criticised the manga for the overuse of the [[moe anthropomorphism]].<ref name="Mania">{{cite web|url=http://www.mania.com/indian-summer-aka-koharu-biyori-vol-01_article_81875.html|title=Indian Summer (aka: Koharu Biyori) Vol. #01|last=Chavez|first=Eduardo M.|date=March 27, 2005|publisher=Mania.com|accessdate=2009-02-21|archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20120930224528/http://www.mania.com/indian-summer-aka-koharu-biyori-vol-01_article_81875.html|archivedate=September 20, 2012}}</ref> Liann Cooper from [[Anime News Network]] criticises the manga for having "no plot" and that the manga's "illustrations look like sloppy sketches".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/right-turn-only/2004-11-20|title=Suger Rush - RIGHT TURN ONLY|last=Cooper|first=Liann|date=November 20, 2004|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=2013-11-16|archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20130929100408/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/right-turn-only/2004-11-20|archivedate=September 29, 2013}}</ref> Anime Fringe's Janet Crooker classifies the manga as a ''[[Chobits]]'' parody.<ref name="AnimeFringe">{{cite web|url=http://www.animefringe.com/magazine/2004/12/short/01.php|title=December 2004 - Manga Shorts|last=Crooker|first=Janet|date=December 2004|publisher=Anime Fringe|accessdate=2013-11-16|archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20120616103926/http://www.animefringe.com/magazine/2004/12/short/01.php|archivedate=June 16, 2012}}</ref> 

{{cquote|"This manga was the material for me. The artwork really doesn't stand out, neither does the dialogue. I think I would have enjoyed it more as a monthly strip, as when condensed, Indian Summer really has no plot progression. It's just a series of episodes where wacky situations happen and panties are shown." - Janet Crooker, Anime Fringe<ref name="AnimeFringe" />}}

Mania.com's Chris Beveridge commends the OVAs for its "character designs are good, the fanservice just right and it plays things at a slightly different angle because of the androids and the lack of a real crush/interest in the main characters".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mania.com/indian-summer-complete-collection_article_112261.html|title=Indian Summer Complete Collection|last=Beveridge|first=Chris|date=April 20, 2009|publisher=Mania.com|accessdate=2009-05-16|archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20121001201846/http://www.mania.com/indian-summer-complete-collection_article_112261.html|archivedate=October 1, 2012}}</ref> THEM Anime's Carlos Ross criticises the OVA for "very juvenile" writing and further comments that the OVA "" is not a cleanly or adroitly written work in regards to pacing". He also criticises the "very abrupt, kludgy transitions (particularly between episodes two and three) that seem to come clean out of left field".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themanime.org/viewreview.php?id=1353|title=Indian Summer|last=Ross|first=Carlos|publisher=THEM Anime|accessdate=2013-11-16|archiveurl=http://wayback.archive.org/web/20130901070600/http://themanime.org/viewreview.php?id=1353|archivedate=September 1, 2013}}</ref>

